                            <comment id="13886435" author="tmueller" created="Thu, 30 Jan 2014 09:19:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Revision 1562749&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13886646" author="tmueller" created="Thu, 30 Jan 2014 15:13:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Reconsidering. It looks like this would be a major compatibility problem, as there seem to be quite many cases where we rely on the old behavior. Also, detection of missing &quot;@&quot; was incomplete (it was ignored in &quot;order by jcr:path&quot;, which was converted to &quot;order by jcr:path/*&quot; which is clearly not what the user wanted).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I guess the easiest solution is to automatically add a &quot;@&quot;, except for &quot;contains(data, &apos;x&apos;)&quot; where &quot;data&quot; is considered to be a node and not a property.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13889528" author="tmueller" created="Mon, 3 Feb 2014 14:58:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Revision 1563940: compatibility with Jackrabbit 2.x&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13896543" author="alex.parvulescu" created="Mon, 10 Feb 2014 13:51:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;bulk close for the 0.16 release&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
